<TITLE> Khaleda bail extended in GATCO case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Tuesday extended former prime minister Khaldea Zia's bail until the disposal of a writ petition in the GATCO graft case. The bench of Syed Mahmud Hossain and Kamrul Islam Siddiqui also ordered an extension of the stay order on the case for same period on her appeal, AAEM Mizanur Rahman, one of Khaleda's lawyers, said. The Anticorruption Commission filed the Global Agro Trade Company (GATCO) case on Sept. 2 last year against BNP chairperson and others. The High Court on July 9 stayed the trial of the case and on Sept. 9 granted Khaleda bail, both for three months. The stay order on the case proceedings was extended for a second time on Aug. 28. The antigraft watchdog filed the case against the former prime minister, son Arafat Rahman Coco and 11 others, on charges of awarding the GATCO a cargo-handling deal through misuse of power. It later pressed charges against a total of 25 people on May 13 this year. Joint forces arrested Khaleda and Coco as accused in the GATCO case on Sept. 3 last year. The case was brought under emergency powers rules on Sept. 18. The case statement alleged that leaving the responsibility of operating the Chittagong port and Kamalapur Railway depots to GATCO caused the state a loss of about Tk 1000 crore. bdnew
